5:
Another day, another patrol!
Let's give it our all, Alk!
9:
Sure... If that's what makes you
happy, then why not.
11: Gave up on the armor, huh?
16:
I've heeded your advice... I don't feel
like passing out from heat stroke
today. Never again...
20:
Glad to see you've come to your
senses about that.
23:
Yes... And I also realized that it's not
good to be too caught up on
custom and how things were done
in the past. I can be a new, modern
knight.
26:
Well, let's go ahead and start our
patrol for the day!
29:
Oh, Sir Gerard! You're dressed much
more casually today!
32:
Indeed. This is my summer style, if
you please!
36:
See, people will accept you no
matter what you're wearing!
43:
Ah, I just remembered. That shop
over there has some limited-time
items for sale! The shaved ice and
fruit were to die for.
46:
There's also a lively pub just around
the corner here. Don't be fooled by
its shabby exterior—the food was
excellent!
49:
Well, look at you! You've basically
been to every place on the island,
huh?
54:
Wh-what are you talking about? I've
merely PATROLLED past these
places, that's all!
58:
Though I suppose, by virtue of
helping so many people, I have also
received a few favors in return.
62:
Why, it would go against the knight's
code of honor to refuse their
warmth and hospitality! I had no
choice!
66:
Hey, I never said that was a bad
thing! It's totally understandable—
69:
Well, looky here! If it isn't my favorite
knight wearing no armor! Hehe,
same outfit today, huh?
71:
Where's the tiger guy from
yesterday? And who's this?
Nice to meetcha, mister!
73:
Y-yes, nice to meet you too!
Are you a friend of Gerard's?
77:
L-let's be on our way, Alk! The patrol
must go on!
80:
Oh you are NOT going to ignore me!
Not after the great time we had last
night!
84:
Oh dear! Too close! My lady you are
too close, please step back! This will
not do!
87:
Haha. That's the same thing you
said yesterday! You've gotta do
better than that!
89:
Hmm. You know, I think I've taken a
liking to you, mister knight!
92:
Y-you... You WHAT?
I thought I made it clear I would
have none of that!
95:
I know. I guess I just like guys who
play hard to get!
99:
H-hard to get? No, absolutely not! I
am doing nothing of the sort!
102:
Are too!
Are you always this thickheaded, or
is it just your helmet? Hehe.
104:
All right then, mister knight! I'm off.
Let's hang out again sometime soon!
107:
... Starting from the very beginning,
tell me EXACTLY what happened last
night.
120:
I swear it! Nothing... of significance
happened between that maiden
and myself!
128:
Alas... I have failed. Beset by
uncertainty and high expectations, I
faltered.
129:
Before I even realized it, I had
started dancing, and singing, and...
making merry.
133: Oh. So, you just... had a good time?
138:
On my name, I swear this, Alk!
Never again shall I engage in such
uncouth behavior!
157:
Leave the rest to me! Flee from this
place at once!
And... one more thing.
159:
I must apologize for my
indiscretion—you see, I am as yet
unversed when it comes to
conversing with women. My
behavior was unbecoming—
161: H-huh?! Is this really the time?
164:
Fear not, for I will protect you!
On my honor as a knight!
172:
"A true knight stands firm, even
before the very jaws of death!"
Come at me, fiend!
179:
Alk, are you all right? I heard that a
monster was on the loose around
here...
183:
I'm fine. Gerard was with me the
whole time, so he took care of it.
187: What is that tinhead doin', exactly?
190:
Say, mister knight... Are you seeing
anyone right now?
193:
Seeing...? N-no! I am a knight first
and foremost! I have no time for—
195:
Right, so you're not. That means I've
got a shot, huh?
199:
W-wait! Stop, please! It would be
most prudent in this situation to
STOP!
203: What the hell is this all about?
208:
That's some girl that Gerard saved,
apparently. It's like something out of
a fairy tale.
212:
Back to bein' all knightly, huh? You
shoulda seen him yesterday.
218:
Nimbus! Pray help me. You are
expertly versed in these sort of
situations, are you not?
223:
Huh? Why the hell would I know?
Clean up your own mess.
232:
A true knight... A true knight...
What does a true knight DO in such
situations?!
